import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="region", y="income", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='Region', ylabel='Income')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    group_sizes = data.groupby('group').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    plt.pie(group_sizes['counts'], labels=group_sizes['group'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.title('What is the proportion of each group in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='pct', hue='region', multiple='stack', kde=True, element='step', stat='density')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of pct across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Region')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='total', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['total'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['total'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['total'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['total'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of total?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
